{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1782800617,"nonce":"NgIiC4H2tRUyv4g1qcXkzsXHCcE=","message":"Audit done; the one genuine functional gap (type codecs) is closed.\n\n## Audit outcome\nThe premise (MySQL silently lagging / leaking pg-isms into core) largely does NOT hold — pg-only behavior is already routed through the Backend trait:\n- pg-only QUERY features are compile-time gated: RETURNING (SupportsReturning), FULL JOIN (SupportsFullJoin), date_trunc/AT TIME ZONE (SupportsDateTrunc). MySQL doesn't impl them, so such code won't compile against a MySQL connection — no silent runtime failures.\n- pg-only DDL (partial/filtered/expression indexes) is rejected with a clean io::Error at render (documented in the README).\n- Dialect divergences are handled correctly via the Dialect seam and work today: NULLS FIRST/LAST emulation, FOR SHARE -\u003e LOCK IN SHARE MODE, ILIKE -\u003e collation, CONCAT, integer division, EXTRACT(SECOND), UPDATE...FROM / DELETE...USING as JOIN, ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE.\n- Prepared statements are intentionally not implemented for MySQL (documented design choice).\n\n## Closed: type codecs (the real gap)\nPostgreSQL had Encode/Decode (behind features) for uuid, JSON, time, chrono, and SystemTime; MySQL had none. Now landed:\n- #66 — uuid (CHAR(36) text) and Json\u003cT\u003e (JSON via serde_json), with canonical_sql_type mapping Uuid-\u003eChar(36) and the wrapper using ColumnType::Json so published columns don't churn.\n- #67 — time::OffsetDateTime, chrono::DateTime\u003cUtc\u003e, and std::time::SystemTime against TIMESTAMP, via the driver's Value::Date (UTC; Mysql::connect pins the session to time_zone='+00:00'). SystemTime uses a dependency-free civil-date algorithm. Out-of-range instants (outside TIMESTAMP's 1970..2038 UTC) are rejected at bind.\n\n## Known MySQL limitations (recorded)\n- Whole-second timestamp resolution (bare TIMESTAMP, fsp 0). Full sub-second precision needs the neutral model to carry fractional precision — split out to bug ec9458d.\n- TIMESTAMP range is 1970..2038 UTC (codecs reject outside it).\n- Partial/filtered/expression indexes, FULL JOIN, date_trunc/AT TIME ZONE, RETURNING, prepared statements: unavailable (compile-time gated or cleanly rejected), as above.\n- MySQL has no expression canonicalization (no canonical.rs equivalent); partial-index/check churn-fidelity is a separate DDL concern (relates to 108fdfc).","files":null}]}